Level 4: Advancing
Create and Use Decorators in Python
Create and apply custom decorators to modify function behavior.
Use Closures and Understand Scoping Rules in Python
Use closures and understand lexical scoping in nested functions, and understand variable scope and name resolution (LEGB rule) to write code that avoids scope-related errors.
Use Inheritance to Extend Python Classes
Implement inheritance in a class to create specialized classes.
Use super() to Call Parent Methods in Python
Use super() to call methods in a parent class.
Implement Multiple Inheritance in Python
Implement multiple inheritance to combine functionality from multiple classes.
Use slots to Create Memory-Efficient Python Classes
Use __slots__ to create memory-efficient classes.
Create Iterators with iter and next in Python
Create a custom iterable class using __iter__ and __next__, and use Python’s iterator protocol explicitly to create custom iterators.
Use Regex in Python to Match Patterns and Extract Text
Use regular expressions for simple pattern matching. Use the re module to match patterns in strings. Extract substrings from text using regular expressions.
Use SQLAlchemy or Another Python ORM
Interact with databases using SQLAlchemy or a similar ORM.
Compare Python Implementations (e.g., CPython, PyPy)
Identify the differences between various Python implementations, such as CPython, PyPy, IronPython, and Jython.
